heading: Primary health care.
general-note: Here are entered works on essential health care made universally accessible to individuals and families in the community by means acceptable to them, through their participation, and at a cost that the community and country can afford. Works on basic or general health care provided usually by a family or general practitioner, internist, pediatrician, obstetrician, gynecologist, physicians' assistant, or nurse practitioner, are entered under. Primary care (Medicine)..
